ZH: 营养是保持健康的重要因素。
EN: Nutrition is an important factor in maintaining health.

ZH: 每天摄取足够的营养对身体健康至关重要。
EN: It is crucial to consume enough nutrients every day for good health.

ZH: 这款食品很有营养，含有丰富的维生素和矿物质。
EN: This food is very nutritious, containing plenty of vitamins and minerals.

ZH: 一些蔬菜和水果富含纤维，有助于保持良好的营养平衡。
EN: Some vegetables and fruits are high in fiber, which helps maintain a good nutritional balance.

ZH: 母亲会为孩子精心准备营养丰富的饭菜。
EN: Mothers prepare nutritious meals for their children carefully.

ZH: 营养学是研究食物对身体的影响的学科。
EN: Nutrition is the study of how food affects the body.

ZH: 有些人需要额外的营养补充品来满足身体的需求。
EN: Some people need additional nutritional supplements to meet their body's needs.

ZH: 每份食物都应该包含均衡的营养成分。
EN: Every meal should consist of a balanced mix of nutrients.

ZH: 运动后及时补充营养可以促进肌肉恢复。
EN: Replenishing nutrients promptly after exercise can promote muscle recovery.

ZH: 幼儿园提供风味美味的午餐，保证学生获得充足的营养。
EN: Kindergartens provide tasty lunches to ensure students receive sufficient nutrition.

ZH: 营养不良会导致身体机能下降。
EN: Malnutrition can lead to a decline in bodily functions.

ZH: 糖尿病患者需要注意饮食，保证摄取足够的营养。
EN: Diabetics need to watch their diet and ensure they consume enough nutrients.

ZH: 每天喝杯牛奶能帮助人体吸收钙质，增加骨密度。
EN: Drinking a glass of milk every day can help the body absorb calcium and increase bone density.

ZH: 妈妈在家做的饭菜比外面餐馆的更加有营养。
EN: Home-cooked meals are more nutritious than those from restaurants.

ZH: 营养饮食可以改善皮肤状况。
EN: A nutritious diet can improve skin condition.

ZH: 学校餐厅提供的午餐应该包含均衡的营养成分。
EN: School cafeterias should provide lunches with a balanced mix of nutrients.

ZH: 为了保持健康，我们需要吃各种富含营养的食物。
EN: To stay healthy, we need to eat a variety of nutrient-rich foods.

ZH: 营养学家建议多吃海鲜，它们富含优质蛋白和不饱和脂肪。
EN: Nutritionists recommend eating more seafood, as they are rich in high-quality protein and unsaturated fats.

ZH: 营养摄入不足会影响免疫系统的正常功能。
EN: Insufficient nutrient intake can affect the normal function of the immune system.

ZH: 饮食中缺乏蛋白质将会导致身体缺乏重要的营养。
EN: A lack of protein in the diet will result in the body lacking essential nutrients.
